other_tests.findings: Bibasilar atelectasis is present; central intrahepatic biliary dilatation; gallbladder distended with surrounding pericholecystic fluid; common bile duct at upper limit of normal measuring 7 mm; normal pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands (left adrenal gland mildly thickened), kidneys with a likely cyst in the left renal cortex; unremarkable stomach, small intestine, colon, and reproductive organs; moderate atherosclerotic disease noted.
